issue.  It  is  a  serious  matter.  It’s  been  lingering  for  quite  awhile, 
and it is something that I will definitely pursue. 

Senator  SMITH.  It’s  very  important,  and  it’s  in  the  interest  of 
Canada  and  the  United  States  that  we  negotiate  a  settlement  so 
that  this  industry,  on  both  sides  of  the  border,  can  survive.  And 
these  duties  that  are  being  collected  are  an  important—a  very  im-
portant part of that negotiated settlement. 

On the issue of piracy, Mr. Gutierrez, America’s copyright indus-
try  generates  some  12  percent  of  American  GDP,  and  account  for 
over  8  percent  of  the  total  U.S.  employment.  Specifically,  the  four 
copyright  categories  are  movies,  music,  publishing,  and  software—
computer  software.  They  account  for  over  $90  billion  in  foreign 
sales  and  exports—more  than  agriculture,  more  than  automobiles, 
and more than aircraft. And there are just untold numbers of peo-
ple  whose  jobs  are  in  jeopardy  because  of  the  amount  of  theft  that 

