is  occurring  overseas  on  American  copyrighted  materials.  And  so, 
I don’t know if you have a comment on that, but I raise this issue, 
because I think it’s so important to highlight to the Department of 
Commerce  that  we  vigorously  pursue  piracy  issues,  specifically 
with  China,  specifically  with  Russia,  where  we  have  lost  billions. 
Pretty soon our entertainers are going to be on street corners with 
monkey-grinders, trying to get people to pay them. But, ultimately, 
if we lose copyright issues, we’re going to lose a great and valuable 
part of the American economy. 

Mr.  GUTIERREZ.  Senator,  I  agree.  And  I  agree  with  the  passion 
